======================================================================
THEORETICAL ANALYSIS: WHY alpha_2 IN {0,4}?
======================================================================

alpha_1=4 means exactly 4 directed odd cycles (counting multiplicity).
These live on some set of vertex-SETS. Multiple directed cycles can
live on the same vertex set (e.g., a 5-vertex set with 3 Hamiltonian cycles).

Case analysis:
  If 4 cycles on 4 distinct vertex sets:
    alpha_2 = sum of products over disjoint pairs
    Each cycle has multiplicity 1. alpha_2 = #disjoint_pairs.
    So alpha_2 in {0,1,2,3,4,5,6} a priori.
    But data shows only {0,4}.

  If 4 cycles on fewer vertex sets (e.g., 2 cycles on one 5-vertex set):
    alpha_2 = sum c_i*c_j for disjoint set-pairs
    Products can be >1.
